knitr document van Steensel lab

LAD rewiring data: CRISPRa in RPE cells – linking DamID changes to mRNA-seq tracks.

Bas van Steensel, Nov 2019.

Introduction

This script plots gene expression related figure panels of Brueckner et al.

Description of Data

  • DamID data preprocessed as in scripts LAD_Rewiring_RPE_CRISPRa_[.]*_BvS[0-9]{6}.Rhtml. Data are average smoothed DamID scores per gene.
  • Genome annotation is Ensembl build 75. This build is a bit old, but it is what the NKI Genomics Core Facility uses for RNAseq data processing.
  • Expression data for 8 targeted genes by Laura Brueckner. Two replicates each.
  • mRNA-seq data re-processed by Tom van Schaik.
  • This script requires a new version of the LAD rewiring functions set: LAD_Rewiring_functions_BvS191112.R or later.

Gene annotation data

Load Refseq annotations and convert to bed format dataframe. The latter is needed for the plotting of gene tracks using the Sushi package.

#Ensembl hg19 build 75 downloaded from    feb2014.archive.ensembl.org/biomart/martview/4c34fe2f4e47c6b55a212cc95e3c952b
#load:
Ensembl.75<-read.delim("./data/ensEMBL/hg19/ensEMBL75_GRCh37.p13.txt", head=TRUE, sep="\t", as.is=TRUE)
#select and rename columns to make a .bed like dataframe:
Ensembl.75<-Ensembl.75[,c(3,4,5,7,6,6,1)]
names(Ensembl.75)<-c("chrom", "start", "stop", "gene", "score","strand","ensembl.gene.id")
#only on full chromosomes:
Ensembl.75<-Ensembl.75[Ensembl.75$chrom %in% c(1:22,"X","Y"),]
#reformat some stuff:
Ensembl.75$chrom<-paste0("chr",Ensembl.75$chrom)
Ensembl.75$strand<-ifelse(Ensembl.75$strand==-1, "-", "+")
#remove redundancies
Ensembl.75<-unique(Ensembl.75)
#remove questionable genes (mostly absent in UCSC):
Ensembl.75<-Ensembl.75[-grep("^RP11", Ensembl.75$gene, value=FALSE),]
Ensembl.75<-Ensembl.75[-grep("^AC[0-9]{6}[.][0-9]*", Ensembl.75$gene, value=FALSE),]
Ensembl.75<-Ensembl.75[Ensembl.75$stop - Ensembl.75$start > 200,] #remove very small genes, as the plotGenes() function of Sushi cannot cope with them
#how many genes in the end:
dim(Ensembl.75)

## [1] 34717     7

#as genomic ranges object:
GeneGR<-makeGRangesFromDataFrame(Ensembl.75)

Conclusion:


Load gene annotations

Refseq gene annotations from UCSC

#gene(s) coordinates:
ggene<-c(); gchrom<-c(); gstart<-c(); gstop<-c()
for(g in names(ExpList)[-1])
{wh<-which(Ensembl.75$gene %in% ExpList[[g]])
 ggene[g]<-g
 gchrom[g]<-as.character(unique(Ensembl.75$chrom[wh]))
 gstart[g]<-min(c(Ensembl.75$start[wh],Ensembl.75$stop[wh]))
 gstop[g]<-max(c(Ensembl.75$start[wh],Ensembl.75$stop[wh]))
}
gchrom<-as.character(gchrom)
names(gchrom)<-ggene
Gcoord<-data.frame(gene=ggene, chrom=gchrom, start=gstart, end=gstop)
print(Gcoord)

Import, average RNAseq data. 

#load RNAseq data:
RNASEQ<-as.data.frame(readRDS("/home/t.v.schaik/mydata/proj/tests/results/ts191029_BigWigs_forLaura/ts191029_BigWigs_forLaura/GRanges_rnaseq_nonzero.rds"))
RSnames<-names(RNASEQ)

#which RNAseq dataset belongs to which targeted gene:
ExS<-list()
ExS[["ctrl"]]<-c("4862_1_CM1502_ATCACGA", "4861_1_CM1502_CGATGTA")
ExS[["ABCB1"]]<-c("4862_2_CM1503_TTAGGCA", "4861_2_CM1503_TGACCAA")
ExS[["ADAM22"]]<-c("4861_10_plb187_CCGTCCC", "4862_10_plb187_GAGTGGA")
ExS[["CCSER1"]]<-c("4861_5_plb170_CAGATCA", "4862_5_plb170_TAGCTTA")
ExS[["GRID2"]]<-c("4861_6_plb171_CTTGTAA", "4862_6_plb171_GGCTACA" )
ExS[["MLK4"]]<-c("4861_8_plb182_AGTTCCG", "4862_8_plb182_GTTTCGG")
ExS[["PCNXL2"]]<-c("4861_7_plb181_AGTCAAC", "4862_7_plb181_GTGGCCT")
ExS[["PTN"]]<-c("4861_3_plb162_ACAGTGA", "4862_3_plb162_ACTTGAA")
ExS[["SOX6"]]<-c("4861_4_plb163_GCCAATA", "4862_4_plb163_GATCAGA")
ExS[["ABCB1_combo"]]<-c("4861_11_plb184_3_GTCCGCA", "4862_11_plb184_3_ACTGATA")

#average replicates:
for(GN in names(ExpList))
  {w<-which(RSnames %in% paste0("X",ExS[[GN]]))
   RNASEQ[,GN] <- (RNASEQ[,w[1]]+RNASEQ[,w[2]])/2
  }

Conclusion: RNAseq data imported and averaged.

Plot comparison of local DamID and Expression data

#Get sgRNA target sequence coordinates:

sgRNA<-read.delim("./data/RPE_CRISPRa_Targets_BvS190514.txt", sep="\t", comment="#", head=TRUE, row.names=1)
print(sgRNA)

for(GN in names(ExpList[-1]))
{print(GN)
 #extract relevant data to pass on to plot function:
 RNAseq.sub<-RNASEQ[,c("seqnames", "start","end","ctrl",GN)]
 names(RNAseq.sub)<-c("chrom", "start", "stop", "ctl", "exp") #rename columns for downstream function
 RNAseq.sub<-RNAseq.sub[RNAseq.sub$chrom==gchrom[GN],] #only relevant chromosome
 RNAseq.sub$exp <- log2(RNAseq.sub$exp+1) #pseudocount 1
 RNAseq.sub$ctl <- -log2(RNAseq.sub$ctl+1) #pseudocount 1

 #load corresponding domainogram:
 load(paste0("./domainograms/EmpiricalDomainogram_chrExp_LAD_rewiring_RPE_", paste0(GN, collapse="+"),"_BvS_",190218,".Rdata"))


 if(GN %in% c("ABCB1", "ADAM22", "ABCB4", "RUNDC3B", "ABCB1_combo"))
    {pg<-ExpList[["ABCB1_combo"]]} #these genes should be plotted in same window
 else {pg<-GN}

 #plot:
 local.RNAseq.plot(RNAseq.sub, DG.Exp, pg, Ensembl.75, mrg.left=8e5, mrg.right=8e5, sgRNA=sgRNA[ExpList[[GN]],"start"],
                             col.exp="darkred", col.ctl="navyblue", col.mrk="#55992F")

 #now as PDF for figure panel:
 pdf(file=paste0("LAD_rewiring_with_RNAseq_track_", paste0(GN, collapse="+"),"_BvS_",Date,".pdf"), width=12, height=7.5, onefile=TRUE)
 local.RNAseq.plot(RNAseq.sub, DG.Exp, pg, Ensembl.75, mrg.left=8e5, mrg.right=8e5, sgRNA=sgRNA[ExpList[[GN]],"start"],
                             col.exp="darkred", col.ctl="navyblue", col.mrk="#55992F")

 #add color key page:
 par(mfrow=c(5,3), mar=c(4,2,4,2))
 plot.color.key.domainogram()
 mtext("color key DamID domainogram", side=3, line=1.8, cex=1)

 dev.off() #close PDF
}
